Refactor the monolithic App.tsx (1831 lines) in C:\Users\User\Documents\citedby-v3 by extracting components into separate files. The goal is to reduce App.tsx to ~400-500 lines while preserving ALL functionality exactly.

IMPORTANT: Read the FULL App.tsx first before making any changes. The file is 1831 lines.

Here's the extraction plan. Create these files in `components/`:

### 1. `components/ToastSystem.tsx` (~50 lines)
Extract from App.tsx:
- The `Toast` interface (line 51-55)
- `ToastContext` creation (line 57-59)
- `useToast` hook export (line 61)
- `ToastContainer` component (line 63-86)
Export: `ToastContext`, `useToast`, `ToastContainer`, `Toast` type

### 2. `components/CommandPalette.tsx` (~110 lines)
Extract the `CommandPalettePanel` component (lines 109-219).
It receives props: `{ onClose: () => void; onNavigate: (view: string) => void }`
Import `Search` from lucide-react.

### 3. `components/ShortcutsModal.tsx` (~40 lines)
Extract the shortcuts modal JSX (lines 969-997).
Component: `ShortcutsModal: React.FC<{ isOpen: boolean; onClose: () => void }>`
Import `X` from lucide-react.

### 4. `components/OnboardingModal.tsx` (~100 lines)
Extract the onboarding modal (lines 839-957).
Component: `OnboardingModal: React.FC<{ show: boolean; onClose: () => void; onNavigate: (view: string) => void }>`
It manages its own `onboardingStep` state internally.
Import `Sparkles`, `Zap` from lucide-react.

### 5. `components/Navbar.tsx` (~250 lines)
Extract the entire `<nav>` element (lines 999-1245).
Component: `Navbar: React.FC<NavbarProps>` where NavbarProps includes:
```typescript
interface NavbarProps {
  user: User | null;
  navbarVisible: boolean;
  animatedCredits: number;
  sessionMinutes: number;
  isMobileMenuOpen: boolean;
  setIsMobileMenuOpen: (v: boolean | ((prev: boolean) => boolean)) => void;
  isSidebarCollapsed: boolean;
  setIsSidebarCollapsed: (v: boolean | ((prev: boolean) => boolean)) => void;
  navigateTo: (view: string) => void;
  onLogout: () => void;
  onOpenCommandPalette: () => void;
  // Notification state
  notifications: Array<{ id: number; type: 'critical' | 'warning' | 'info' | 'success'; title: string; time: string; unread: boolean }>;
  isNotifOpen: boolean;
  setIsNotifOpen: (v: boolean) => void;
  notifRef: React.RefObject<HTMLDivElement>;
  // Quick actions
  isQuickActionsOpen: boolean;
  setIsQuickActionsOpen: (v: boolean) => void;
  quickActionsRef: React.RefObject<HTMLDivElement>;
  // Profile
  isProfileOpen: boolean;
  setIsProfileOpen: (v: boolean) => void;
  profileRef: React.RefObject<HTMLDivElement>;
}
```
Import all needed lucide icons (LogOut, Zap, Plus, Menu, Fuel, Bell, Search, X, UserIcon, Clock, etc.)
Import `LanguageSelector` from '../i18n'
Import `useTranslation` from '../i18n'
Import `User` type from '../types'

### 6. `components/Sidebar.tsx` (~120 lines)
Extract the desktop sidebar (lines 1287-1320) and mobile sidebar (lines 1249-1284).
Also extract the `NavItem` subcomponent (lines 745-785).
Component: `Sidebar: React.FC<SidebarProps>` where:
```typescript
interface SidebarProps {
  currentView: string;
  navigateTo: (view: string) => void;
  isSidebarCollapsed: boolean;
  isMobileMenuOpen: boolean;
  setIsMobileMenuOpen: (v: boolean) => void;
}
```
Import needed lucide icons and `useTranslation`.

### 7. `components/MobileBottomNav.tsx` (~50 lines)
Extract the mobile bottom navigation bar (lines 1742-1772).
Component: `MobileBottomNav: React.FC<{ currentView: string; navigateTo: (view: string) => void; isMobileMenuOpen: boolean }>`

### 8. `components/AppFooter.tsx` (~60 lines)
Extract the footer (lines 1774-1825).
Component: `AppFooter: React.FC<{ user: User | null; navigateTo: (view: string) => void }>`
Import `Zap` from lucide-react, `useTranslation` from '../i18n'.

### After extraction, App.tsx should contain:
- Imports of all extracted components
- `useAnimatedNumber` hook (lines 89-107) - keep inline, it's small
- `PLAN_LIMITS` constant
- `App` component (I18nProvider wrapper)
- `AppContent` component with:
  - All useState/useEffect for state management
  - All handler functions (handleAnalyze, handleRecharge, handleLogin, etc.)
  - The render method using extracted components
  - The page routing switch (currentView === 'xxx' blocks)

CRITICAL RULES:
- Preserve ALL functionality exactly - no behavior changes
- Keep all the same class names and styling
- Do NOT modify any page components in pages/
- Use proper TypeScript types for all props
- Use default exports where the original used them
- Import `User` type from '../types' where needed
- The `useTranslation` hook is from '../i18n' (exports `t`, `tf`, `locale`)
- Write all new component files
- Then write the refactored App.tsx
- Do NOT run build

